OL,4,Crecorded in 2024, say campaigners
OL,6,FIt was the first full year that 100%
OL,7,Fof storm overflows had been monitored
OL,8,Fand the figures revealed that although
OL,9,Fthe number of spills fell slightly
OL,10,Fcompared with 2023, the duration of
OL,11,Fsewage discharges was up.
OL,13,FThere were 450,398 recorded spills `
OL,14,Fwhich should only take place in
OL,15,F"exceptional circumstances" to prevent
OL,16,Fsewers being overwhelmed in heavy
OL,17,Frainfall and backing up into homes `
OL,18,Fin 2024, compared with 464,056 in 2023.
